sari: You made it through the first wave. Good.
sari: Those creatures you fought — they used to be people. Office workers, students, parents.
sari: Online gambling took everything from them. When there's nothing left to lose, people stop being themselves.
sari: Did you notice how the Bats flash in patterns? That's not random.
sari: Gambling platforms use the exact same trick — lights, sounds, and "near win" moments designed to fool your brain.
sari: A near-win feels like a real win. Your brain releases the same chemicals. So you try again. And again.
sari: The Frogs are living slot machines. Every fight makes you feel like the next one will finally pay off.
sari: It won't. That's the design. Engineered addiction — not entertainment.
sari: "Free credits." "Guaranteed jackpot." All of it is bait. The house ALWAYS wins. Mathematically. By design.
sari: The Witch is the most dangerous. She finds people at their lowest and offers a lifeline.
sari: It is not a lifeline. It is a chain — with interest rates that grow faster than anyone can pay.
sari: Clear eyes. That is your strongest weapon out here.
